const designGuide = `## UI/UX Design Principles for Web Applications

### Layout
- Main interaction element must be centered and visually dominant (40-60% of viewport)
- Use vertical single-column layouts for game/app UIs — never side-by-side grids unless it's a dashboard
- Content hierarchy: hero/main action → stats/feedback → secondary actions (shop, settings)
- Mobile-first: everything should work on a 375px wide screen and scale up
- Scrollable secondary content (shops, lists) should never push the main interaction off-screen

### Visual Feedback
- Every user interaction (click, purchase, hover) MUST produce visible feedback
- Number changes should animate (bounce, scale pulse, color flash)
- Buttons: press animation (scale 0.95), hover glow/lift, disabled state with reduced opacity
- Success actions: green flash, checkmark, particle burst
- Use CSS transitions (200-300ms) on all interactive elements

### Color & Contrast
- Dark backgrounds with bright accent colors for maximum contrast
- Use gradients over flat colors for depth (e.g., purple-900 to indigo-950)
- Interactive elements should be the brightest items on screen
- Affordability: green = can buy, red/gray = locked, gold = premium
- Text must have sufficient contrast — white/yellow on dark, with text-shadow for readability

### Typography
- Big, bold numbers for scores/stats (text-4xl to text-6xl)
- Clear hierarchy: title (bold, large) → subtitle (medium) → body (regular, smaller)
- Use font-weight differences, not just size, to create hierarchy
- Monospace or tabular numbers for counters that change frequently

### Animation
- Idle animations (slow pulse, float, rotate) make the UI feel alive
- Click animations should be fast (100-200ms) and snappy
- Spawn/death animations for appearing/disappearing elements (scale 0→1, fade in/out)
- Use CSS will-change on animated elements for performance
- Stagger animations for lists (each item slightly delayed)

### Cards & Containers
- Rounded corners (border-radius: 12-16px)
- Subtle shadows for depth (shadow-lg, shadow-xl)
- Semi-transparent backgrounds with backdrop-blur for overlay panels
- Hover: lift (translateY -2 to -4px) + shadow increase
- Border: subtle (1px border with low-opacity white or accent color)`;

